We formulate the model description to address the above decision-making procedure. Let x(t) and a be the control variable at time t and parameter with uncertainty, respectively. We define the uncertainty as a set of discrete scenarios S = {s}, where each scenario s has a probability P(s) at t = 0 and a(s) represents the parameter a in a scenario s. The objective function to be maximized is represented by f(x(t) | a(s)). If the perfect ex ante information is available at t = 0, then we need only to determine the optimal decision under the certain scenario s*. This is represented by the case (a) of Fig. 2. The optimal behavior x*(t | s*) is given by the optimal solution of1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
